## 8. Repo-specific rules (load on demand)

Do not apply NestJS DDD rules to FastAPI services. Do not use `mui-frontend` on `ucl-web/`.

| Repo | Skill | Rule file |
| ---- | ----- | --------- |
| `uc-talent-backend/` | `implement-backend` | `backend-architecture`, `backend-coding-standards`, `backend-project-architechture` |
| `uc-backend-fastapi/`, `uc-embedding-fastapi/` | `implement-fastapi` | `backend-fastapi` |
| `uc-frontend-nextjs-v1/`, `uc-ats-react-app/` | `implement-frontend`, `mui-frontend` | `frontend-coding-standards` |
| `ucl-web/` | `implement-ucl-web` | `ucl-web-frontend` |
| `ucl-web-cms/` | `implement-strapi-cms` | `strapi-cms` |

Backend V2 only under `uc-talent-backend/src/modules/*` — not legacy `src/domains/*`. Do not create migrations or DDL unless the user explicitly approves.

For fullstack tickets, backend owns the API contract; frontend must consume the confirmed contract.

